      <div type="translation">
        <p>Success!</p>
        <p n="1" rend="stanza">In the eleventh year of the king, the lord
					Ehavalaśrī, on the auspicious eleventh day of the bright
					fortnight of (month) Māgha,</p>
        <p n="2" rend="stanza"> the excellent Talavara Eliśrī,
					of bright intellect, whose intense devotion (is directed)
					towards the god Kumāra, the son of Fire, of fierce strength,
					grandson of the general Aṇikki who was victorious in battles
					and whose fame is widely known, son of Gāṇḍi, by the grace
					of Kārttikeya made (this) temple, abounding in good fortune,
					the abode of Sarvadeva (i.e. Śiva).</p>
      </div>
